      • addData

        public void addData(Solution<?> solution,
                    int generationNumber,
                    double repeatNumber)
        Add data to plot. Only use when the problem is single objective.

        The plot will be drawing using the generationNumber int the axis X and the objective in the axis Y.

        For each repetition of the algorithm a different color to show the points will be used.

        Parameters:
        solution - the solution
        generationNumber - number used in the x-axis. It indicates the number of generations in the current executed repetition of algorithm.
        repeatNumber - This number indicate the repeat number of the algorithm.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if solution is null

      • addData

        public void addData(List<? extends Solution<?>> solutionList)
        Add data to plot. Only use if the number of objectives is 2. The plot was between objective1 and objective2.
        Parameters:
        solutionList - the solution
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if solutionList is null
        IllegalStateException - if call this method with the instance of this class is a single objective
